The schema describes API responses from the OpenWeather Current Weather Data API from https://openweathermap.org/current. It is an object type. The main properties of the schema are: 'coord' is an object that contains required fields 'lat' (a number) and 'lon' (a number). 'weather' is an array of objects, each with required fields 'id' (an integer), 'main' (a string), 'description' (a string), and 'icon' (a string). 'base' is a string. 'main' is an object with properties: 'temp' (a number), 'feels_like' (a number), 'temp_min' (a number), 'temp_max' (a number), 'pressure' (a number), 'humidity' (a number), 'sea_level' (a number), and 'grnd_level' (a number). 'visibility' is an integer. 'wind' is an object containing required fields 'speed' (a number) and 'deg' (a number). 'clouds' is an object that contains a required field 'all' (a number with a minimum of 0). 'dt' is a number. 'sys' is an object with required fields 'type' (an integer), 'id' (an integer), 'message' (a number), 'country' (a string), 'sunrise' (an integer), and 'sunset' (an integer). 'timezone' is an integer. 'id' is an integer. 'name' is a string. 'cod' is an integer. All properties are required. No additional properties are allowed at the root level.涫
